# Patch 0025 — Kavacha Customization Studio, Advanced tier: live custom-CSS
# editor with history + safe mode (ROADMAP Phase 3 "Live CSS editor with history
# + safe mode"; ADR 0009).
#
# WHAT: KavachaUserCSS.sys.mjs is userChrome.css done safely — the user's chrome
# CSS is applied LIVE as a per-window AUTHOR_SHEET (the chrome-only windowUtils
# mechanism from 0012/0022/0023; never touches web content, never gains script),
# every save snapshots the previous text to kavacha-usercss-history.json so any
# change is revertible, and a SAFE MODE pref (kavacha.usercss.safe-mode) disables
# ALL custom CSS so a broken rule can never brick the UI. The Studio grows an
# "Advanced" tab (editor + Apply/Revert + history list + safe-mode toggle); a
# palette command "Toggle Custom CSS Safe Mode" reaches the escape hatch even if
# the chrome is unusable.
#
# RUNTIME SHAPE (shared with 0022/0023; ADR 0008): process singleton init() +
# per-window applyToWindow() from ZenStartup, applyToAllWindows() driven by a
# kavacha.usercss.revision doorbell the content editor bumps. The Studio page is
# a tab's content document, so the chrome AUTHOR_SHEET never styles the editor
# itself — the editor stays usable even while the user's CSS is (mis)styling the
# surrounding chrome.
#
# NOT BUILD-VERIFIED: authored against the post-0024 tree. Run `git apply --check`
# + Marionette (apply a rule, see the chrome change; toggle safe mode; revert
# from history) before marking verified. Adds KavachaUserCSS.sys.mjs; touches
# src/zen/common/moz.build, ZenStartup.mjs, KavachaCommandRegistry.sys.mjs,
# zen-command-palette.ftl, and studio.html/js/css from 0024. Applies on top of
# 0024.
